title: 1978 United States Senate elections
added: Democrat [[Dick Clark (senator)|Dick Clark]] decided to run for re-election to a second term, but was defeated by [[Roger Jepsen]], the Republican nominee and former Lieutenant Governor of Iowa.

title: 1978 United States Senate elections
added: Republican [[Dewey F. Bartlett]] retired instead of seeking a second term. In the elections, Democratic nominee [[Davis Boren]] won the open seat over Republican [[Robert B. Kamm]].
